snippet.textDisplay: Finally a breezy pop number! This is beautifully sung by Ali Khan (Gave me a feel of those English pop numbers in early 2000s esp. Westlife!). My moment of the composition is at 4:20 when the scale changes from A# major to C major and how smartly they devised it by bringing the melody to G note which is common in both the scales and continued with C major scale after a pause! I am sure it's Jaffer Zaidi's handiwork. Overall loved the arrangement and the use of Strings section to give that breezy feel!
snippet.textOriginal: Finally a breezy pop number! This is beautifully sung by Ali Khan (Gave me a feel of those English pop numbers in early 2000s esp. Westlife!). My moment of the composition is at 4:20 when the scale changes from A# major to C major and how smartly they devised it by bringing the melody to G note which is common in both the scales and continued with C major scale after a pause! I am sure it's Jaffer Zaidi's handiwork. Overall loved the arrangement and the use of Strings section to give that breezy feel!
